"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151947","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-10-28","<p>The sale of vaccines is regulated by the Human Medicines Regulations 2012. The regulations apply without distinction to the National Health Service and the private healthcare sector. As prescription only medicines, the general rule is that they may only be sold or supplied to an individual by or under the supervision of a pharmacist on registered pharmacy premises against a prescription written by an independent prescriber. There are some exceptions to these restrictions for example, to allow a doctor to supply directly to a patient.</p><p>The majority of vaccines are injectable which means they can only be administered by or in accordance with the directions of an independent prescriber.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Mid Bedfordshire","Ms Nadine Dorries",,"2019-10-28T16:35:13.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151947/answer","Biography information for Ms Nadine Dorries","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151947/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151947/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-23","Vaccination: Private Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what regulations apply to the sale of vaccinations by private companies.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","4291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151948","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-10-28","<p>I am aware that The Gambia is planning on bringing a case before the International Court of Justice as part of an Organisation of Islamic Cooperation initiative but I have not had any discussions with my Gambian counterpart on this issue.</p><p>​</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-10-28T17:13:49.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151948/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151948/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151948/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-10-23","Burma: Genocide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with this Gambian counterpart on a potential case of genocide against Burma being brought to the International Court of Justice.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","4410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151949","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-11-01","<p>It is not possible to assess the trends in the prevalence of lipoid pneumonia since the introduction of vaping. This is because there is insufficient data to identify this trend.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill",,"2019-11-01T12:20:29.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151949/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151949/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151949/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-10-23","Electronic Cigarettes: Pneumonia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of trends in the prevalence of lipoid pneumonia since the introduction of vaping.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","4411"
