"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151440","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-10-29","<p>The department records all fires in prison on an electronic national database that comprises information specific to the circumstances surrounding each individual event. As part of this, prison fire-related referrals to the police are recorded and are held centrally by HMPPS. However, as confirmed in the response to 550, Crown Prosecution Service referrals are not held centrally by HMPPS because such referrals are made by the police. The requested data may, therefore, be held by individual police forces.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","3675 ; 3676","2019-10-29T15:20:53.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151440/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151440/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151440/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-10-22","Prisons: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 21 October 2019 to Question 550 on Prisons: Fires, what information his Department holds on fire related events in prison.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","3674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151441","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-28","<p>£592,073,452.22 has been spent through the Public Sector Resourcing framework since it commenced in January 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The breakdown of the workers day rates in the requested categories (accurate as of 23 October 2019) is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Day Rate Category for Public Sector Resourcing Framework</p></td><td><p>Number of contingent workers per band</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>less than £200 per day</p></td><td><p>7698</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£201 - £500 per day</p></td><td><p>3602</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£501 - £1000 per day</p></td><td><p>2937</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>£1001 - £2000 per day</p></td><td><p>76</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>&gt;£2000 per day</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>It would not be appropriate for the Government to share commercially sensitive information into the public domain in relation to question 3547.</p><p> </p>","Carmarthen West and South Pembrokeshire","Simon Hart","3547 ; 3548","2019-10-28T17:25:27.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151441/answer","Biography information for Simon Hart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151441/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151441/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-10-22","Cabinet Office: Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of October 21 to Question 888 on Cabinet Office: Temporary Employment, what the total cost is of hiring those 14,190 contingent workers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","3546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151442","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-10-29","<p>The department records all fires in prison on an electronic national database that comprises information specific to the circumstances surrounding each individual event. As part of this, prison fire-related referrals to the police are recorded and are held centrally by HMPPS. However, as confirmed in the response to 550, Crown Prosecution Service referrals are not held centrally by HMPPS because such referrals are made by the police. The requested data may, therefore, be held by individual police forces.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","3674 ; 3676","2019-10-29T15:20:53.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151442/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151442/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151442/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-10-22","Prisons: Fires","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Answer of 21 October 2019 to Question 550 on Prisons: Fires, why the number of referrals for fire related events in prison is not held centrally.","false","Biography information for Mary Glindon","North Tyneside","Mary Glindon","3675"
