"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151457","Department for Education","false","2019-10-29","<p>We recognise the importance of care leavers being well prepared to deal with the challenges of living independently at a young age, which includes having good budgeting skills. Care leavers have to be more independent and resilient than young people who live with their parents. My officials will contact the Share Foundation to discuss their request in more detail.</p><p> </p>","Chippenham","Michelle Donelan",,"2019-10-29T13:16:59.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151457/answer","Biography information for Michelle Donelan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151457/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1151457/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-10-22","Children in Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will provide The Share Foundation with support in identifying young people who would benefit from the Stepladder of Achievement programme; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","3684"
